column2: Consent Statement  Please review the following information about this study.   	 	TASK: If you agree to participate in this study, we will ask you to answer a series of questions about a series of images.  	 	 	BENEFITS:  There will be no direct benefits to you other than compensation. 	 	 	RISKS: We don't anticipate any risks from participating in this study to be greater than normal activity. 	 	 	PRIVACY:  No personally identifying information will be revealed to anyone other than the researchers conducting this study. The records of this study will be kept private. We do not collect any personally-identifying information.   	 	 	SECURITY: All records pertaining to this research are stored on encrypted servers. Only the researchers will have access to the records. 	 	 	CHOICE:  Participating in this study is completely voluntary. If you decline to participate, it will not affect your current or future relationship with the researchers. 	 	 	WITHDRAWAL: If you agree to participate, you are free to withdraw at any time. You can withdraw by closing the browser window. If you withdraw, your responses will not be recorded.  	 	 	QUESTIONS: You may ask any questions about the research at any time. If you have questions about the research after you complete the task, please contact Arvind Satyanarayan. 	 	 	QUESTIONS: If you are not satisfied with response of research team, have more questions, or want to talk with someone about your rights as a research participant, you should contact the MIT Committee on the Use of Humans as Experimental Subjects (COUHES).
